cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on question answering using memory networks and distributed sentence vector representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as end-to-end memory networks, which suggests it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of distributed sentence vector representations could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of Skip-Thought Vectors, which are often used in natural language processing tasks such as text classification and sentiment analysis, which could also place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision) as this sub-category often deals with image and text analysis.
